    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>MILITARY CONTRACT SECURED</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By William A. Orme Jr.</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Orme, William A Jr</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Israeli Aircraft Industries, state-owned military contractor, wins $270 million contract to build spy satellite for Turkey based on its own Ofek reconnaissance (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A state-owned military contractor, Israeli Aircraft Industries, won a $270 million contract to build a spy satellite for Turkey based on its own Ofek reconnaissance satellite, company officials said yesterday, confirming Turkish news reports. France's Alcatel had also bid for the contract. The Israeli company is competing against United States and European concerns for a $4 billion helicopter order and a $1 billion airborne radar contract scheduled to be awarded by the Turkish military this year.</p>
        <p>William A. Orme Jr.</p>
      </block>
